    "costs": "10000000",
    "actions_taken": [
      "Manual Emergency Shut Down (ESD) initiated by control room operators",
      "Platform bleed down performed",
      "Personnel mustered",
      "Wells shut in and facility made safe",
      "Firewater piping section isolated",
      "USCG, NRC, and BSEE notified",
      "Dorado flowline and internal gas lift repaired and returned to production",
      "Platform firewater piping repaired and returned to service"
    ],
    "summary": "On 04 May 2025 at 0445 hours, the 178-foot supply vessel M/V Adriatic struck the Marlin Tension Leg Platform (VK 915 A) operated by Anadarko Petroleum Corporation. The vessel's captain was preparing paperwork for a drift test and not focused on navigation. The second captain had been given permission to leave the bridge, leaving no one actively steering the vessel. The bow contacted the Northwest pontoon and the right stern contacted the Southwest pontoon, damaging two production risers (Dorado and Crown and Anchor), a gas lift line, and firewater piping. The platform was manually ESD'd and production was shut in. No injuries or pollution occurred. Estimated damage exceeded $10 million.",
    "recommendations": [
      "BSEE NOD recommends the Office of Incident Investigation (OII) issue a Safety Alert on this incident",
      "Safety Alert should reach personnel who work on boats/vessels that service facilities, not just operators on the facility"
    ],
